summary: An Ordinance approving the assessment roll of Local Improvement District No. 1930, for the improvement of Thirty-second Avenue and Thirty-third Avenue, each from the north line of Albion Heights Addition to The City of Seattle, to East Howell Street; and certain parts of certain other streets and avenues therein named, all in the City of Seattle, by grading and curbing the same and constructing concrete walks and the construction of all necessary drains and the adjusting of all manholes, etc., necessary, and by the construction of a concrete walk on the south side of East Pine Street from Thirty-fifth Avenue to the east line of Buchanan's Addition, under Ordinance No. 19848 and the same now stands, be, and the same is, hereby in all things approved.
